Step 1: Find the Net Profit.  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,095,371.35.  

Step 2: Calculate the average Owner’s Equity.  
• From the balance sheet, the beginning Total Owner’s Equity is 13,000,000.00 and the ending Total Owner’s Equity is 14,095,371.35.  
• Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 14,095,371.35) / 2  
               = 27,095,371.35 / 2  
               ≈ 13,547,685.68  

Step 3: Compute ROE.  
• ROE = (Net Profit) / (Average Owner’s Equity)  
    = 1,095,371.35 / 13,547,685.68  
    ≈ 0.0809 or 8.09%

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) is approximately 8.09%.
